Design a complete high-fidelity responsive web application UI/UX for an AI-powered chatbot information service for Kerja Praktik (KP) and Magang at Dinas Kelautan dan Perikanan Provinsi Jawa Timur.

PROJECT NAME:
DKP Assistant

SYSTEM PURPOSE:
The website is a public information portal and AI chatbot service that helps students and vocational school students obtain accurate information about Kerja Praktik and Magang services.

The chatbot uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and answers questions based only on official documents, SOPs, requirements, FAQs, guidelines, and knowledge base documents managed by administrators.

The system must include:
1. Public Landing Page
2. Dedicated Chatbot Page
3. Admin Authentication
4. Admin Dashboard
5. Knowledge Base Management
6. Document Upload and Indexing
7. Conversation Logs
8. Unanswered Questions Management
9. User Feedback Management
10. Chatbot Analytics
11. Chatbot Settings

Create all required desktop screens and reusable components.

==================================================
DESIGN SYSTEM
==================================================

Create a professional, modern, trustworthy Indonesian government public service website.

Visual identity:
- Inspired by Dinas Kelautan dan Perikanan Provinsi Jawa Timur.
- Marine, fisheries, government digital service identity.
- Primary colors: dark navy blue, ocean blue, teal, cyan.
- White and light gray backgrounds.
- Soft blue gradient accents.
- Avoid excessive gradients.
- Use subtle marine-inspired visual elements.
- Clean and modern government service appearance.

Typography:
Use a modern sans-serif font such as Inter.

Design characteristics:
- Clean.
- Professional.
- Minimal.
- Modern.
- Accessible.
- Trustworthy.
- Spacious layouts.
- Consistent 8px spacing system.
- Large border radius: 12px–20px.
- Subtle shadows.
- Clear information hierarchy.
- WCAG-friendly color contrast.

Create reusable components and variants for:
- Buttons.
- Input fields.
- Dropdowns.
- Search bars.
- Navigation.
- Sidebar.
- Cards.
- Tables.
- Modals.
- Toast notifications.
